  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3872191277" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8051792-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544530609p2/8051792.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3872191277?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/8051792-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8051792-lisa?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8051792-lisa?shelf=buddy-reads-greg">buddy-reads-greg</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3872191277" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6210550095856391351">[3.8] I appreciated learning about Garfield as a man and politician - especially the look at the presidential nominating process and the behind the scenes power struggles by Roscoe Conkling. I was particularly fascinated by the overview of scientific advances of the time, and the frustrating struggle to save Garfield&apos;s life. A bit melodramatic at times, especially in the buildup to his assassination, but Millard&apos;s skillful narrative kept me engaged.</span>
  <span id="freeText6210550095856391351" style="display:none">[3.8] I appreciated learning about Garfield as a man and politician - especially the look at the presidential nominating process and the behind the scenes power struggles by Roscoe Conkling. I was particularly fascinated by the overview of scientific advances of the time, and the frustrating struggle to save Garfield's life. A bit melodramatic at times, especially in the buildup to his assassination, but Millard's skillful narrative kept me engaged.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6210550095856391351" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

